# CF_B25EFS711_Java FullStack

Course Code: B25EFS711
Category: CS-Core
L-T-P-C: 3-0-4
Credits: 3
Prerequisites: Basic programming (Java or equivalent), Databases fundamentals, HTML/CSS basics
Contact Hours: 42 (Lecture) + 28 (Lab/Project)

## 1. Course Overview
This course equips students with skills to design and build end-to-end web applications using Java-based backend technologies and modern frontend frameworks. Emphasis is on RESTful APIs, persistent storage, security basics, cloud deployment, and fullstack integration with hands-on labs and a capstone mini-project.

## 2. Learning Objectives (High-level)
- Build scalable Java backend services using Spring Boot.
- Design RESTful APIs and integrate with frontend SPAs.
- Implement persistent storage with relational databases and JPA.
- Apply authentication, authorization, and basic web security practices.
- Deploy and monitor applications on cloud or container platforms.
- Collaborate on a small fullstack project following agile practices.

## 3. Course Outcomes (COs)
On successful completion, students will be able to:

- CO1: Explain fullstack architecture and design RESTful services. (Apply)
- CO2: Develop backend applications with Spring Boot and JPA. (Apply)
- CO3: Build responsive frontend single-page applications using a modern JS framework and consume REST APIs. (Apply)
- CO4: Implement authentication & authorization and secure common web vulnerabilities. (Analyze)
- CO5: Deploy, containerize, and monitor applications in a cloud or container environment. (Apply)
- CO6: Work in a team to deliver a small end-to-end fullstack project with CI/CD basics. (Create)

